title: Troll Axe Visibility
story: dungeo
description: Tests that the axe is held by troll, can't be taken (white-hot), and both vanish on death

---

# The conscious troll strikes bystanders each turn (MDL melee canon) and can
# kill a score-0 player outright. RETRY restores the turn-0 snapshot and
# revives the engine on death (same pattern as debug-combat).
[RETRY: max=5]

# Get lantern first; ND = immortality (the conscious troll's bystander blows
# can kill a score-0 player — this tests axe visibility, not mortality)
> GDT
[OK: contains "GDT"]

> tk brass lantern
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> nd
[OK: contains "Immortality"]

> ex
[OK: contains "Returning"]

> turn on lantern
[OK: contains "on"]

# Get to the Troll Room
> GDT
[OK: contains "GDT"]

> AH Troll Room
[OK: contains "Teleported"]

> ex
[OK: contains "Returning"]

> look
[OK: contains "Troll Room"]
[OK: contains "troll"]

# Verify axe can be examined (it's held by troll)
> examine axe
[OK: contains "bloody axe"]

# Can't take it - white-hot while troll lives
> take axe
[OK: contains "white-hot"]

# Kill the troll
> GDT
[OK: contains "GDT"]

> KL troll
[OK: contains "Killed"]

> ex
[OK: contains "Returning"]

# Both troll and axe should be gone (vanish in black smoke, MDL)
> look
[OK: contains "Troll Room"]
[OK: not contains "troll blocks"]
[OK: not contains "bloody axe"]

# Can't examine axe - it's gone
> examine axe
[OK: contains "can't see"]

[END RETRY]
